gave me the drug and not candy.

621
00:41:16,080 --> 00:41:17,810
There's candy?

622
00:41:17,820 --> 00:41:19,390
Eat something green,
and we'll talk.

623
00:41:19,380 --> 00:41:23,140
So, we're, uh, rooting for
nausea there, huh?

624
00:41:23,150 --> 00:41:26,490
Well, okay. Um...

625
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:32,850
I'm just all left thumbs
when it comes to this stuff.

626
00:41:32,850 --> 00:41:36,290
Mm, you're doing great, dad.
No, I don't know about that.

627
00:41:36,280 --> 00:41:38,980
Your mom were here,
she'd know just what to say.

628
00:41:38,980 --> 00:41:40,710
Me?

629
00:41:40,720 --> 00:41:44,350
I can fix the toaster.

630
00:41:44,350 --> 00:41:47,150
Well, maybe just, uh...

631
00:41:47,150 --> 00:41:51,220
Do you think maybe...
You could watch Molly for a bit?

632
00:41:52,480 --> 00:41:54,310
I just don't --
I'm not sure

633
00:41:54,320 --> 00:41:56,220
if I can keep my eyes open
right now...
Okay.

634
00:41:56,220 --> 00:41:58,350
For some reason.

635
00:41:58,350 --> 00:41:59,850
Watch who?

636
00:41:59,850 --> 00:42:01,290
Me!

637
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:03,180
Who?
Me!

638
00:42:03,180 --> 00:42:04,540
Well, what the heck?

639
00:42:04,550 --> 00:42:05,850
Thank you, dad.

640
00:42:05,850 --> 00:42:08,150
Hmm. Yeah, sure.
You get some rest.

641
00:42:08,150 --> 00:42:10,550
We'll just be here, uh,
eatin' sugar cereal

642
00:42:10,550 --> 00:42:13,720
